- following this tut: http://adrianmejia.com/blog/2012/09/11/backbone-dot-js-for-absolute-beginners-getting-started/
- cd into backbone-chat/
- npm install
- npm install -g browserify watchify
- run: watchify static/index.js -o static/bundle.js
- the above command appears to hang, just leave it running
- make a python virtualenv
- then pip install -r requirements.txt
- export FLASK_APP=app.py
- export FLASK_DEBUG=1
- flask run
- open: http://localhost:5000/
